1
00:00:14,500 --> 00:00:15,467
Mrs. Madrigal?

2
00:00:16,167 --> 00:00:17,067
I'm sorry, Ma'am.

3
00:00:17,133 --> 00:00:18,433
Mrs. Madrigal wants me
to tell you

4
00:00:18,500 --> 00:00:22,300
that it's not the right time
for her to socialize with you.

5
00:00:22,367 --> 00:00:24,667
And please respect her privacy.

6
00:00:24,733 --> 00:00:25,700
I'm sorry, Ma'am.

7
00:00:25,767 --> 00:00:28,700
I know that you two
love each other.

8
00:00:28,767 --> 00:00:31,300
Don't doubt your relationship.

9
00:00:31,367 --> 00:00:34,567
Would you fight for it
if it wasn't real?

10
00:00:34,667 --> 00:00:37,133
Look at what happened
after I did that.

11
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:39,433
My mother disowned me.

12
00:00:39,500 --> 00:00:44,500
I lost my mom, my baby, and now
I'm afraid I will lose Red too.

13
00:00:44,567 --> 00:00:47,767
Okay, I'll let this slide.

14
00:00:47,833 --> 00:00:50,900
But you have to do
something for me.

15
00:00:50,967 --> 00:00:52,033
What the?

16
00:00:52,100 --> 00:00:53,000
Oh my God!

17
00:00:54,500 --> 00:00:55,367
What is that?

18
00:00:55,433 --> 00:00:57,900
Who told you to serve that?

19
00:00:57,967 --> 00:01:00,833
Only one person is
capable of doing this.

20
00:01:00,900 --> 00:01:02,500
Someone who keeps sending us
all sorts of things.

21
00:01:04,333 --> 00:01:05,533
It's Amanda.

22
00:01:05,600 --> 00:01:07,667
Why? What happened?

23
00:01:07,767 --> 00:01:09,600
Someone threatened my mom.

24
00:01:09,667 --> 00:01:11,867
Only your mom is capable
of doing it!

25
00:01:11,933 --> 00:01:14,300
Yen, I tried to respect
your mom.

26
00:01:14,367 --> 00:01:16,667
If she doesn't stop,
I will forget she's your mom.

27
00:01:16,733 --> 00:01:17,733
I might end up hurting her.

28
00:01:17,800 --> 00:01:19,400
You are cordially invited

29
00:01:19,467 --> 00:01:24,833
to the home of Mr. and Mrs.
Lucho Madrigal.

30
00:01:24,900 --> 00:01:28,033
Ladies and gentlemen,
my beautiful wife,

31
00:01:28,100 --> 00:01:29,267
Mrs. Madrigal.

32
00:01:35,567 --> 00:01:36,967
Mrs. Madrigal.

33
00:01:37,033 --> 00:01:39,333
We've got so much in common.

34
00:01:39,400 --> 00:01:42,667
I liked that hat too when
I saw it at the shop.

35
00:01:42,767 --> 00:01:44,533
See that? I told you.

36
00:01:44,600 --> 00:01:46,300
We could really be good friends.

37
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:00,867
Really?

38
00:02:04,333 --> 00:02:05,033
Amanda?

39
00:02:06,267 --> 00:02:09,333
Were you the one who was
supposed to buy this hat?

40
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:11,433
What happened?
Why didn't you buy it?

41
00:02:12,233 --> 00:02:13,367
Are you short on money?

42
00:02:16,100 --> 00:02:17,367
This cannot be.

43
00:02:17,433 --> 00:02:17,867
No.

44
00:02:20,633 --> 00:02:21,567
Love...

45
00:02:22,633 --> 00:02:24,500
I was just kidding.

46
00:02:24,567 --> 00:02:28,667
Like what Mrs. Ramos said,
we're friends.

47
00:02:47,633 --> 00:02:48,167
Right?

48
00:02:54,433 --> 00:02:55,200
Hey, what?

49
00:02:56,300 --> 00:02:57,000
What's wrong?

50
00:02:59,167 --> 00:03:02,333
I thought you were
desperate to meet me.

51
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:04,700
You've been chasing me around,
remember?

52
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:07,900
Come on.

53
00:03:09,300 --> 00:03:11,267
How come you don't
look happy to see me?

54
00:03:16,100 --> 00:03:16,633
Excuse us.

55
00:04:44,733 --> 00:04:46,067
Hey, what's that?

56
00:04:47,767 --> 00:04:49,133
My gosh.

57
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:51,567
Don't keep it all to yourself.

58
00:04:51,633 --> 00:04:56,267
You might get drunk and get in
trouble with Yenyen again.

59
00:04:58,933 --> 00:04:59,700
About that...

60
00:05:00,500 --> 00:05:02,900
I'm sorry for getting you
involved.

61
00:05:03,967 --> 00:05:04,967
It's okay.

62
00:05:05,033 --> 00:05:07,600
I'm sorry if I caused
you guys trouble.

63
00:05:08,267 --> 00:05:10,667
I didn't mean to
cause any trouble.

64
00:05:10,733 --> 00:05:11,900
No, it's not your fault.

65
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:17,667
If anything, I want to thank you
for listening to my rants.

66
00:05:17,733 --> 00:05:19,600
Even though we spent all night

67
00:05:19,667 --> 00:05:22,867
talking about my problem
with Yenyen.

68
00:05:22,933 --> 00:05:23,900
It's okay.

69
00:05:23,967 --> 00:05:26,033
Just don't do it again.

70
00:05:27,233 --> 00:05:30,200
It's not that I don't want
to talk about Yenyen but...

71
00:05:30,933 --> 00:05:32,700
I just don't like
seeing you sad.

72
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,467
You should cheer up
because this is a party.

73
00:05:37,467 --> 00:05:38,200
Come on.

74
00:05:39,200 --> 00:05:39,933
How about this...

75
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:44,900
to make you smile,
let's take a picture.

76
00:05:47,167 --> 00:05:49,333
Come on, cheese!

77
00:05:51,967 --> 00:05:52,767
See?

78
00:05:55,533 --> 00:05:57,067
Your smile is so cute.

79
00:05:57,133 --> 00:05:58,033
I miss it.

80
00:05:59,567 --> 00:06:02,533
Let's not talk about anything
sad for tonight, okay?

81
00:06:04,967 --> 00:06:06,400
Let's go, cheers!

82
00:06:12,267 --> 00:06:14,800
I can't blame him if
he's still mad at me.

83
00:06:15,867 --> 00:06:17,967
We've been through a lot,
Raichu.

84
00:06:19,867 --> 00:06:21,000
I also don't know

85
00:06:21,067 --> 00:06:23,100
if my mom is the one who's been
messing with Aunt Rina.

86
00:06:27,033 --> 00:06:29,900
It's just hard to believe it.

87
00:06:29,967 --> 00:06:31,900
It's as if your mom
turned into a terrorist.

88
00:06:32,700 --> 00:06:33,867
She loves you so much.

89
00:06:35,433 --> 00:06:36,600
She loves me so much?

90
00:06:38,033 --> 00:06:39,033
So what do you call

91
00:06:39,100 --> 00:06:41,867
all those scary gifts
she's been sending me?

92
00:06:41,967 --> 00:06:43,700
Yes, she loves me.

93
00:06:43,767 --> 00:06:48,633
If you can love someone so much,

94
00:06:48,700 --> 00:06:51,667
that's how much you can
hate her too.

95
00:06:52,567 --> 00:06:56,000
So are you saying
the more you love,

96
00:06:56,067 --> 00:06:57,000
the more you hate?

97
00:06:57,067 --> 00:06:58,567
But it doesn't seem right.

98
00:06:58,633 --> 00:07:00,667
That's what happened
to my mom and me.

99
00:07:02,100 --> 00:07:04,867
So are you saying
that you hate her too?

100
00:07:04,933 --> 00:07:07,333
Is it wrong to hate her?

101
00:07:07,400 --> 00:07:09,267
After all the things she's done?

102
00:07:10,367 --> 00:07:13,100
She's the reason my child died!

103
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:17,300
She's the reason Red
and me don't get along.

104
00:07:18,167 --> 00:07:19,200
She cursed me.

105
00:07:19,267 --> 00:07:20,400
She wanted me to
become miserable.

106
00:07:20,467 --> 00:07:21,867
What kind of a mother does that?

107
00:07:23,033 --> 00:07:24,100
Easy. Calm down.

108
00:07:24,167 --> 00:07:25,200
That's enough.

109
00:07:25,267 --> 00:07:26,233
I don't want you to get sick.

110
00:07:26,933 --> 00:07:30,467
I'm going to find some memes
to humor you.

111
00:07:34,100 --> 00:07:35,433
This one's funny.

112
00:07:41,767 --> 00:07:42,367
Hey, why?

113
00:07:43,700 --> 00:07:45,900
- Why are you so quiet?
- It's nothing.

114
00:07:45,967 --> 00:07:46,800
Why?

115
00:07:53,200 --> 00:07:53,667
Hey!

116
00:07:54,300 --> 00:07:55,600
Where are you going?

117
00:08:12,433 --> 00:08:13,400
Oh my God, Victor.

118
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:16,633
This can't be real.

119
00:08:16,700 --> 00:08:19,033
Is this some kind
of a sick joke?

120
00:08:21,900 --> 00:08:24,467
Amanda can't be Mrs. Madrigal.

121
00:08:27,133 --> 00:08:29,400
I thought I saw a ghost.

122
00:08:29,467 --> 00:08:30,600
It is a ghost!

123
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:33,233
She should be dead by now!

124
00:08:35,833 --> 00:08:37,167
I can't believe it.

125
00:08:38,267 --> 00:08:44,833
But at the same time,
I am so sure she's Amanda.

126
00:08:47,033 --> 00:08:50,267
But she's far different
from the Amanda we know.

127
00:08:50,333 --> 00:08:52,733
You saw how sophisticated
Mrs. Madrigal is.

128
00:08:52,800 --> 00:08:53,667
She's elegant.

129
00:09:09,433 --> 00:09:12,233
Can anyone change in that
short amount of time?

130
00:09:13,067 --> 00:09:15,033
That's what we need to find out.

131
00:09:16,533 --> 00:09:17,733
I mean,

132
00:09:17,800 --> 00:09:22,067
it's obvious that she married
a rich man to have money.

133
00:09:22,133 --> 00:09:24,033
To change herself.

134
00:09:25,500 --> 00:09:26,567
But the question is...

135
00:09:28,267 --> 00:09:32,500
does Lucho Madrigal know what
sort of person he married?

136
00:09:33,900 --> 00:09:36,333
That's what you need
to find out, Victor.

137
00:09:36,400 --> 00:09:37,167
Why me?

138
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:39,800
Can we just leave it be, Rina?

139
00:09:39,867 --> 00:09:41,567
We could be wrong.

140
00:09:41,633 --> 00:09:44,333
She could be someone
who resembles Amanda.

141
00:09:44,400 --> 00:09:45,967
I don't want to
embarrass myself.

142
00:09:47,100 --> 00:09:48,633
You just need to ask him.

143
00:09:49,700 --> 00:09:51,333
You have to do this, Victor.

144
00:09:52,900 --> 00:09:55,767
We have to confirm
our suspicions.

145
00:09:57,900 --> 00:09:59,867
Because if that's Amanda...

146
00:10:01,900 --> 00:10:04,267
she didn't return
just to look pretty.

147
00:10:06,467 --> 00:10:08,400
She's back for revenge, Victor.

148
00:10:13,133 --> 00:10:14,833
Okay, I'll do it.

149
00:10:16,200 --> 00:10:18,567
But we have to be careful.

150
00:10:18,633 --> 00:10:19,833
This is their territory.

151
00:10:55,567 --> 00:10:56,500
Amanda.

152
00:10:58,567 --> 00:11:03,667
You can't deny that
you're Amanda.

153
00:11:05,233 --> 00:11:10,733
Didn't you give me a card
from AM?

154
00:11:12,067 --> 00:11:13,900
Amanda Madrigal.

155
00:11:14,900 --> 00:11:20,800
I never denied anything, Rina.
I never said I was not Amanda.

156
00:11:23,500 --> 00:11:23,967
Why?

157
00:11:26,133 --> 00:11:27,567
Can't you believe it?

158
00:11:29,033 --> 00:11:34,967
Because you expect to see me
as a homeless person.

159
00:11:35,033 --> 00:11:38,200
Or you're probably thinking
I'm already dead.

160
00:11:39,467 --> 00:11:44,467
Because you pushed me to
commit suicide, remember?

161
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:49,633
Yes, I remember.

162
00:11:51,600 --> 00:11:56,133
And I also remember
where you came from.

163
00:11:57,933 --> 00:11:58,967
You were poor...

164
00:12:01,033 --> 00:12:02,333
and a slave.

165
00:12:04,600 --> 00:12:09,333
And no matter what jewelry
you adorn yourself with,

166
00:12:12,133 --> 00:12:16,467
it will never change your past.

167
00:12:17,867 --> 00:12:20,500
Remember, Amanda...

168
00:12:21,533 --> 00:12:23,733
a snake remains a snake

169
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:30,433
no matter how many times
it sheds its skin.

170
00:12:30,500 --> 00:12:33,200
At least the snake
becomes more beautiful

171
00:12:33,267 --> 00:12:35,000
after it sheds its skin.

172
00:12:35,067 --> 00:12:37,267
They become shinier.

173
00:12:37,333 --> 00:12:38,667
Unlike someone I know...

174
00:12:39,800 --> 00:12:41,300
that looks haggard.

175
00:12:41,367 --> 00:12:43,333
Like I heard from the
boutique's manager...

176
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:46,300
it's as if the haggardness is
caused by financial problems.

177
00:12:48,200 --> 00:12:49,700
You witch!

178
00:13:03,400 --> 00:13:06,967
I'm not the same Amanda
you used to oppress.

179
00:13:38,500 --> 00:13:39,767
I won't waste my time on you.

180
00:13:41,233 --> 00:13:41,933
Actually...

181
00:13:43,500 --> 00:13:46,067
I don't care about
the past anymore.

182
00:13:46,967 --> 00:13:49,333
It's over. I've moved on.

183
00:13:51,233 --> 00:13:52,367
Really?

184
00:13:52,433 --> 00:13:53,633
Of course.

185
00:13:56,367 --> 00:14:00,300
Look around you. I'm so blessed.

186
00:14:00,367 --> 00:14:02,067
There's nothing I could ask for.

187
00:14:04,167 --> 00:14:06,767
If there's somebody
I should be thankful for,

188
00:14:08,100 --> 00:14:10,533
it's you.

189
00:14:11,533 --> 00:14:15,200
I wouldn't have met my husband
if you didn't push me away.

190
00:14:15,267 --> 00:14:19,900
If you didn't make my
life miserable before,

191
00:14:19,967 --> 00:14:22,800
I wouldn't be where I am now.

192
00:14:22,867 --> 00:14:23,800
So...

193
00:14:27,100 --> 00:14:28,300
thank you, Rina.

194
00:14:30,733 --> 00:14:32,100
Thank you so much.

195
00:14:35,067 --> 00:14:36,000
Okay, that's enough.

196
00:14:36,067 --> 00:14:37,367
I have to mingle
with my other guests.

197
00:14:37,433 --> 00:14:38,633
Enjoy the party.

198
00:14:39,433 --> 00:14:40,467
What about Eden?

199
00:14:43,267 --> 00:14:49,933
Have you moved on
without your daughter?

200
00:14:55,533 --> 00:14:57,533
I've accepted the fact that
she's happy with your family.

201
00:14:58,467 --> 00:15:01,000
So I won't force her
to come back to me.

202
00:15:03,767 --> 00:15:05,867
Actually, it's better that way.

203
00:15:07,433 --> 00:15:09,900
Because now all I have
to think about is...

204
00:15:12,067 --> 00:15:14,633
how to spend
my husband's money.

205
00:15:16,533 --> 00:15:17,333
Thanks again.

206
00:15:25,167 --> 00:15:26,300
Is there anything else
you want to say to me?

207
00:15:47,233 --> 00:15:48,400
Here, Bro. Have a drink.

208
00:15:53,833 --> 00:15:54,500
So how's business?

209
00:15:55,600 --> 00:15:57,733
It's good.
Our sales went up a little.

210
00:15:57,800 --> 00:15:58,500
I'm happy.

211
00:16:04,600 --> 00:16:05,400
Victor!

212
00:16:05,467 --> 00:16:06,433
Come here, join us.

213
00:16:11,500 --> 00:16:12,333
Excuse me.

214
00:16:12,400 --> 00:16:13,400
I'll just talk to my wife
real quick.

215
00:16:13,467 --> 00:16:13,933
Okay.

216
00:16:14,933 --> 00:16:15,700
Come on, Bro.

217
00:16:16,433 --> 00:16:17,267
Enjoy the party.

218
00:16:18,033 --> 00:16:18,400
Here.

219
00:16:23,467 --> 00:16:25,233
I want to talk to you.

220
00:16:27,267 --> 00:16:28,267
Is there a problem?

221
00:16:32,100 --> 00:16:35,533
How did you meet Mrs. Madrigal?

222
00:16:36,567 --> 00:16:38,000
Her name is Amanda, right?

223
00:16:39,800 --> 00:16:40,700
My wife?

224
00:16:42,400 --> 00:16:42,967
How?

225
00:16:47,233 --> 00:16:50,700
It's a long story,
but to make it short...

226
00:16:53,200 --> 00:16:56,300
our wives don't like each other.

227
00:16:58,033 --> 00:17:00,633
Amanda's daughter lives with us.

228
00:17:01,900 --> 00:17:03,200
She is my son's girlfriend.

229
00:17:04,467 --> 00:17:06,900
Did Amanda say something
about it?

230
00:17:09,800 --> 00:17:13,100
I don't know a lot
about my wife's past,

231
00:17:13,933 --> 00:17:17,400
but we've known each other
for a long time.

232
00:17:17,500 --> 00:17:20,000
I had known her before I went
abroad and became rich.

233
00:17:21,800 --> 00:17:23,533
She doesn't like to
talk about her past

234
00:17:23,600 --> 00:17:24,700
and everything that
happened to her.

235
00:17:24,767 --> 00:17:25,167
That's why...

236
00:17:26,767 --> 00:17:27,800
I don't ask her about it.

237
00:17:29,967 --> 00:17:31,233
But now that you're here...

238
00:17:32,467 --> 00:17:37,200
perhaps I can learn from you
what happened to her.

239
00:17:41,867 --> 00:17:43,633
You know...

240
00:17:43,633 --> 00:17:48,200
me and Yenyen used to be
so happy together.

241
00:17:49,767 --> 00:17:52,167
We always took
each other's sides.

242
00:17:52,233 --> 00:17:54,833
And we're even so excited
to have our baby.

243
00:17:56,033 --> 00:17:59,467
But now, we often fight.

244
00:18:00,833 --> 00:18:04,733
I feel like we're
drifting apart.

245
00:18:04,800 --> 00:18:06,433
I don't know what to do.

246
00:18:10,633 --> 00:18:12,467
I have regrets, yes.

247
00:18:13,367 --> 00:18:18,533
I shouldn't have taken my anger
with her mom out on her.

248
00:18:20,733 --> 00:18:26,800
Red, it's only human to lose
your cool and get mad

249
00:18:26,900 --> 00:18:28,300
when you've had enough.

250
00:18:29,100 --> 00:18:33,367
And if Yenyen really loves you,
she will understand that.

251
00:18:36,833 --> 00:18:37,300
Well...

252
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:41,833
sorry if I somehow
ruined your mood.

253
00:18:43,067 --> 00:18:45,033
You know, it's okay.
You can leave me here.

254
00:18:45,100 --> 00:18:46,567
You can go back inside.

255
00:18:46,633 --> 00:18:47,867
Oh, come on.

256
00:18:47,933 --> 00:18:51,600
How can I enjoy myself inside?
The room is full of oldies.

257
00:18:52,800 --> 00:18:54,733
Come on, Red. Let's go.

258
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:56,067
Let's have a good time.

259
00:18:57,500 --> 00:19:02,200
And didn't you tell me we're not
going to talk about sad things?

260
00:19:02,267 --> 00:19:02,967
You know what?

261
00:19:03,767 --> 00:19:05,367
Why don't we listen to music?

262
00:19:06,267 --> 00:19:07,100
Okay?
Come on.

263
00:19:09,933 --> 00:19:10,433
Game.

264
00:19:12,633 --> 00:19:13,600
Wait. Here.

265
00:19:13,667 --> 00:19:15,200
Come on, hurry up!

266
00:19:15,267 --> 00:19:18,067
Let's dance! Let's go!
Oh, this is your favorite.

267
00:19:18,133 --> 00:19:19,867
- Come on!
- Sab, no.

268
00:19:19,933 --> 00:19:20,900
Come on!

269
00:19:20,967 --> 00:19:23,667
Don't stop yourself
from having a good time.

270
00:19:23,733 --> 00:19:26,767
If you have fun, you'll be in
a better mood when you go home.

271
00:19:26,833 --> 00:19:28,633
So you and Yenyen
won't have a fight.

272
00:19:28,733 --> 00:19:30,033
Let's go, come on!

273
00:19:30,100 --> 00:19:31,633
That's your favorite. Come on.

274
00:19:31,700 --> 00:19:33,400
- Okay.
- Yes!

275
00:19:34,700 --> 00:19:35,633
Yes.

276
00:19:36,367 --> 00:19:37,500
I'll be honest.

277
00:19:38,967 --> 00:19:43,167
Amanda and Rina used to fight
often because of our children.

278
00:19:44,633 --> 00:19:47,667
But it stopped when
Amanda went missing.

279
00:19:48,733 --> 00:19:50,967
We have no idea what
happened to her.

280
00:19:52,467 --> 00:19:53,667
What about Amanda's daughter?

281
00:19:54,767 --> 00:19:57,133
She's with us.
She's living with us.

282
00:19:57,200 --> 00:19:58,767
We're taking good care of her.

283
00:20:00,267 --> 00:20:02,400
Rina treats her as her own.

284
00:20:04,300 --> 00:20:05,533
I'm glad to hear that.

285
00:20:07,867 --> 00:20:12,933
Amanda told me that her
daughter was doing well.

286
00:20:13,900 --> 00:20:16,700
That's why she doesn't
want to bother her.

287
00:20:35,100 --> 00:20:36,467
Excuse me?

288
00:20:36,533 --> 00:20:40,300
Do you know Red Ramos?
Rina Ramos' son.

289
00:20:40,367 --> 00:20:41,233
Yes.

290
00:20:41,300 --> 00:20:42,633
Rina is my friend.

291
00:20:42,700 --> 00:20:44,267
Are you her son's girlfriend?

292
00:20:47,067 --> 00:20:49,100
I haven't seen Cecille yet.

293
00:20:49,167 --> 00:20:51,067
She's been looking for you.

294
00:20:51,133 --> 00:20:53,567
She'll ask you again to go
shopping with her tomorrow.

295
00:20:53,633 --> 00:20:54,667
There she is.

296
00:20:57,633 --> 00:20:59,167
You're underdressed, Dear.

297
00:21:00,500 --> 00:21:02,633
I'm just looking for Red.

298
00:21:02,700 --> 00:21:03,900
Have you seen him?

299
00:21:05,367 --> 00:21:06,667
I saw him going out.

300
00:21:07,433 --> 00:21:08,733
Maybe he's in the garden.

301
00:21:08,833 --> 00:21:10,167
Try to look for him there.

302
00:21:11,133 --> 00:21:11,833
Okay.

303
00:21:11,900 --> 00:21:14,367
Excuse me. I'll just go to her.

304
00:21:28,300 --> 00:21:29,267
Ma'am.

305
00:21:29,333 --> 00:21:30,333
Oh, thank you, thank you.

306
00:21:33,600 --> 00:21:34,933
Cecille.

307
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:36,500
Amanda!

308
00:21:36,567 --> 00:21:38,633
What a beautiful party!

309
00:21:38,700 --> 00:21:39,700
Thank you.

310
00:21:39,767 --> 00:21:40,733
Are you enjoying it?

311
00:21:41,333 --> 00:21:42,667
Oh, yes!

312
00:21:42,767 --> 00:21:43,400
Like this?

313
00:21:43,467 --> 00:21:45,067
Okay, okay.

314
00:21:45,133 --> 00:21:46,167
Wait, it's a bit...

315
00:21:46,233 --> 00:21:46,867
And then on the other side.
- There, okay.
- Okay.

316
00:21:47,900 --> 00:21:49,000
- And then on the other side.
- Okay.

317
00:21:49,067 --> 00:21:50,500
- I kind of forgot the steps.
- On the other side.

318
00:21:50,567 --> 00:21:51,633
Let's turn around.

319
00:21:51,700 --> 00:21:53,300
- Okay, turn around.
- Turn around, turn around.

320
00:21:53,367 --> 00:21:54,067
Reverse.

321
00:21:54,133 --> 00:21:55,567
Reverse.

322
00:21:55,633 --> 00:21:56,867
- I'm getting dizzy.
- Turn around again.

323
00:21:59,067 --> 00:22:00,733
- Oh my God!
- Turn around again.

324
00:22:10,467 --> 00:22:11,000
Red!

325
00:23:05,133 --> 00:23:07,733
I already know the weakness
of their relationship.

326
00:23:07,800 --> 00:23:09,333
And I can use that against them.

327
00:23:09,400 --> 00:23:12,733
And mark my words, Colby.
Red will come back to me.

328
00:23:12,800 --> 00:23:15,833
Thank you for taking care of me
when I was pregnant.

329
00:23:15,900 --> 00:23:19,967
But now that my baby is gone,
I have no reason to stay here.

330
00:23:21,000 --> 00:23:24,067
Looks like there's also no hope
for Red and me.

331
00:23:24,167 --> 00:23:25,167
- What?
- What?

332
00:23:25,233 --> 00:23:27,000
Did you know what she's
going through right now?

333
00:23:27,867 --> 00:23:29,167
It's unimaginable.

334
00:23:29,233 --> 00:23:32,600
She lost her baby
after giving birth.

335
00:23:32,667 --> 00:23:33,433
What?

336
00:23:33,500 --> 00:23:35,767
Only one person can hurt
my daughter.

337
00:23:35,833 --> 00:23:36,367
It's Rina.

338
00:23:36,433 --> 00:23:38,533
Didn't you curse them?

339
00:23:38,600 --> 00:23:40,067
It's your fault!

340
00:23:40,133 --> 00:23:41,133
That's not true.

341
00:23:46,133 --> 00:23:49,000
I knew it!
You haven't changed, Amanda!

342
00:23:49,067 --> 00:23:50,700
You still behave
like a prisoner!

343
00:23:50,767 --> 00:23:52,700
You think you're better than me?

344
00:23:52,767 --> 00:23:56,533
You may be wealthy,
but you have no class!

345
00:23:56,633 --> 00:23:58,133
Leave me alone! Stop it!

346
00:23:58,200 --> 00:23:59,233
Amanda!
